    "description": "Kawasaki Geological Engineering Co., Ltd. provides geological survey services in Japan and internationally. The company offers geological surveys, including ground analysis and evaluation, underground gas survey, indoor testing, and measurement and exploration using boreholes; maintenance services, such as survey of underground cavities and buried objects, countermeasures and design, concrete diagnosis, and asset management of anchor slopes. It also provides analysis and design comprising river embankment, levee stability analysis, and levee design, as well as groundwater analysis and landslide disaster site surveying, investigation, analysis, and design. In addition, it provides ocean, resources, and energy-related services, which include 2D and 3D sonic exploration and data processing, seabed topography and surface surveys, autonomous underwater vehicle and tethered remotely operated vehicle, submarine gravimeter, and ocean bottom microtremor array survey. Further, the company is involved in disaster prevention and mitigation, such as slope disaster and ground movement monitoring systems, disaster response, and electromagnetic and sweep source for seismic reflection surveys; and research and development comprising technology and equipment development analysis and human resource development. Kawasaki Geological Engineering Co., Ltd. was founded in 1943 and is headquartered in Minato, Japan."
